article.description: Taze Moore posted 13 points as Cal State Bakersfield easily defeated Cal Poly 72-50 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Moore scores 13 to lift CS Bakersfield over Cal Poly 72-50
article.linkText: Moore scores 13 to lift CS Bakersfield over Cal Poly 72-50
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Taze Moore posted 13 points as Cal State Bakersfield easily defeated Cal Poly 72-50 on Saturday night. De'Monte Buckingham had eight rebounds for Cal State Bakersfield (6-8), which ended its five-game road losing streak. Cal Poly put up 20 first-half points, a season low for the team. Kyle Colvin had 8 points for the Mustangs (2-10). Cal State Bakersfield plays Texas Tech on the road next Sunday. Cal Poly plays San Diego State on the road next Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
